Reasoning: The paper discusses attention in the context of visual perception, which suggests that it is likely to be categorized under computer vision (cs.CV). The use of short-term memory and the development of a new model also suggest that it could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The training method using stochastic variational inference suggests it could also be categorized under neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Finally, the consideration of how a model interacts with its input and the constraints imposed on it suggest that the paper could also be relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
